<paragraph id="8BF636A2567AFFCEFF7C4E49B1C71582" blockId="16.[164,779,1850,1903]" lastBlockId="16.[826,1441,660,1263]" pageId="16" pageNumber="650">
<emphasis id="B93DEAB0567AFFCEFF7C4E49B3861622" box="[164,398,1850,1871]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="650">Emended diagnosis:</emphasis>
The following character combination is diagnostic for 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D21567AFFCEFE624E2AB03D1603" authorityName="Perez-Miles &amp; Locht" authorityYear="2003" box="[442,565,1881,1902]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hemirrhagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="650" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gertschi">
<emphasis id="B93DEAB0567AFFCEFE624E2AB03D1603" box="[442,565,1881,1902]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="650">H. gertschi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Male palpal bulb with slender embolus similar in length to tegulum (
<figureCitation id="13722A27567AFFCEFC9A4BC1B1CB13A5" box="[834,963,690,712]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="12.[164,243,744,763]" captionTargetBox="[392,1210,205,707]" captionTargetId="figure-0@12.[387,1219,196,713]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 11. Hemirrhagus gertschi Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, holotype male LAAH, left palpal bulb. A, retrolateral view. B, prolateral view. C, dorsal view. D, ventral view. Abbreviations: SA, subapical keel; VG, ventral groove. Scale bar = 1 mm." pageId="16" pageNumber="650">Fig. 11A, B</figureCitation>
), 
<collectionCode id="ED58AE67567AFFCEFC014BC0B1F213A5" box="[985,1018,691,712]" country="France" name="Museum national d'Histoire Naturelle, Laboratiore de Paleontologie" pageId="16" pageNumber="650">SA</collectionCode>
ends at retrolateral face of embolus; VG deep. The posterior curvature of 
<collectionCode id="ED58AE67567AFFCEFB3C4BA2B70D138B" box="[1252,1285,721,742]" country="France" name="Museum national d'Histoire Naturelle, Laboratiore de Paleontologie" pageId="16" pageNumber="650">SA</collectionCode>
occurs in the base of the embolus and forms an angle of 90° (
<figureCitation id="13722A27567AFFCEFC9A4A7DB1CE1249" box="[834,966,782,804]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="12.[164,243,744,763]" captionTargetBox="[392,1210,205,707]" captionTargetId="figure-0@12.[387,1219,196,713]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 11. Hemirrhagus gertschi Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, holotype male LAAH, left palpal bulb. A, retrolateral view. B, prolateral view. C, dorsal view. D, ventral view. Abbreviations: SA, subapical keel; VG, ventral groove. Scale bar = 1 mm." pageId="16" pageNumber="650">Fig. 11A–D</figureCitation>
). Metatarsus I curved (
<figureCitation id="13722A27567AFFCEFB2B4A7DB7501249" box="[1267,1368,782,804]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="11.[144,223,1762,1781]" captionTargetBox="[303,1264,932,1732]" captionTargetId="figure-51@11.[303,1264,932,1732]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 10. Hemirrhagus gertschi Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, holotype male LAAH. A, carapace, dorsal view. B, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). C, opisthosoma, dorsal view. D, metatarsus I, prolateral view. E, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. F, labial and maxillary cuspules. G, tibial apophyses, prolateral view. H, tibial apophyses, ventral view. Scale bars = 2 mm (A–D), 1 mm (E–H)." pageId="16" pageNumber="650">Fig. 10D</figureCitation>
). Rap and Pap slightly reduced (
<figureCitation id="13722A27567AFFCEFBB24A5EB6F9122F" box="[1130,1265,813,835]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="11.[144,223,1762,1781]" captionTargetBox="[303,1264,932,1732]" captionTargetId="figure-51@11.[303,1264,932,1732]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 10. Hemirrhagus gertschi Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, holotype male LAAH. A, carapace, dorsal view. B, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). C, opisthosoma, dorsal view. D, metatarsus I, prolateral view. E, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. F, labial and maxillary cuspules. G, tibial apophyses, prolateral view. H, tibial apophyses, ventral view. Scale bars = 2 mm (A–D), 1 mm (E–H)." pageId="16" pageNumber="650">Fig. 10G, H</figureCitation>
). Ocular tubercle reduced, all eyes normally developed; periocular pigmentation strongly marked on AME (
<figureCitation id="13722A27567AFFCEFAED4A19B14612F3" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="11.[144,223,1762,1781]" captionTargetBox="[303,1264,932,1732]" captionTargetId="figure-51@11.[303,1264,932,1732]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 10. Hemirrhagus gertschi Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, holotype male LAAH. A, carapace, dorsal view. B, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). C, opisthosoma, dorsal view. D, metatarsus I, prolateral view. E, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. F, labial and maxillary cuspules. G, tibial apophyses, prolateral view. H, tibial apophyses, ventral view. Scale bars = 2 mm (A–D), 1 mm (E–H)." pageId="16" pageNumber="650">Figs 10A, E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13722A27567AFFCEFC864AFAB1B912F3" box="[862,945,905,926]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="12.[164,243,1762,1781]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,981,1732]" captionTargetId="figure-39@12.[323,1283,981,1732]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 12. Hemirrhagus gertschi Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, paratype female LAAH. A, carapace, dorsal view. B, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). C, opisthosoma, dorsal view. D, trochanter I lateral scopular setae (LSC), ventral view. E, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. F, spermathecae, dorsal view. Scale bars = 4 mm (A, C), 2 mm (B), 1 mm (D–F)." pageId="16" pageNumber="650">12A, E</figureCitation>
). Urticating setae arranged in two dorsal paramedian patches as bands along the opisthosoma, brown in colour, without well-defined margins (
<figureCitation id="13722A27567AFFCEFC9A4A97B1A21294" box="[834,938,996,1018]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="11.[144,223,1762,1781]" captionTargetBox="[303,1264,932,1732]" captionTargetId="figure-51@11.[303,1264,932,1732]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 10. Hemirrhagus gertschi Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, holotype male LAAH. A, carapace, dorsal view. B, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). C, opisthosoma, dorsal view. D, metatarsus I, prolateral view. E, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. F, labial and maxillary cuspules. G, tibial apophyses, prolateral view. H, tibial apophyses, ventral view. Scale bars = 2 mm (A–D), 1 mm (E–H)." pageId="16" pageNumber="650">Figs 10C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13722A27567AFFCEFC604A97B1E01297" box="[952,1000,996,1018]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="12.[164,243,1762,1781]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,981,1732]" captionTargetId="figure-39@12.[323,1283,981,1732]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 12. Hemirrhagus gertschi Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, paratype female LAAH. A, carapace, dorsal view. B, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). C, opisthosoma, dorsal view. D, trochanter I lateral scopular setae (LSC), ventral view. E, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. F, spermathecae, dorsal view. Scale bars = 4 mm (A, C), 2 mm (B), 1 mm (D–F)." pageId="16" pageNumber="650">12C</figureCitation>
). Spermathecae paired, slightly fused at the base; receptacles strongly sclerotized apically, broad at base and slightly bent laterally (
<figureCitation id="13722A27567AFFCEFAEB4D52B79D1555" box="[1331,1429,1057,1080]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="12.[164,243,1762,1781]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,981,1732]" captionTargetId="figure-39@12.[323,1283,981,1732]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 12. Hemirrhagus gertschi Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, paratype female LAAH. A, carapace, dorsal view. B, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). C, opisthosoma, dorsal view. D, trochanter I lateral scopular setae (LSC), ventral view. E, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. F, spermathecae, dorsal view. Scale bars = 4 mm (A, C), 2 mm (B), 1 mm (D–F)." pageId="16" pageNumber="650">Fig. 12F</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D21567AFFCEFCE24D33B63B1538" authorityName="Perez-Miles &amp; Locht" authorityYear="2003" box="[826,1075,1088,1109]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hemirrhagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="650" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gertschi">
<emphasis id="B93DEAB0567AFFCEFCE24D33B63B1538" box="[826,1075,1088,1109]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="650">Hemirrhagus gertschi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from most 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D21567AFFCEFAD14D33B1821518" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hemirrhagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="650" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B93DEAB0567AFFCEFAD14D33B7A91538" box="[1289,1441,1088,1109]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="650">Hemirrhagus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by the posterior curvature of 
<collectionCode id="ED58AE67567AFFCEFB2D4D2CB71E1519" box="[1269,1302,1119,1140]" country="France" name="Museum national d'Histoire Naturelle, Laboratiore de Paleontologie" pageId="16" pageNumber="650">SA</collectionCode>
forming an angle of 90°. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D21567AFFCEFBAD4D0DB6FD15FF" authorityName="Perez-Miles &amp; Locht" authorityYear="2003" box="[1141,1269,1149,1171]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hemirrhagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="650" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papalotl">
<emphasis id="B93DEAB0567AFFCEFBAD4D0DB6FD15FF" box="[1141,1269,1149,1171]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="650">H. papalotl</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D21567AFFCEFAF64D0DB7A915FF" authority="Mendoza Marroquín, 2014" authorityName="Mendoza Marroquín" authorityYear="2014" box="[1326,1441,1149,1171]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hemirrhagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="650" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valdezi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B93DEAB0567AFFCEFAF64D0DB7A915FF" box="[1326,1441,1149,1171]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="650">H. valdezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20E57CB567AFFCEFCE24DEFB19C15DC" box="[826,916,1180,1201]" pageId="16" pageNumber="650" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by having the urticating setae arranged in two dorsal paramedian patches as bands along the opisthosoma.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF636A2567AFFCEFCE24C65B7A91426" blockId="16.[826,1441,1302,1355]" pageId="16" pageNumber="650">
<emphasis id="B93DEAB0567AFFCEFCE24C65B6CB1446" box="[826,1219,1302,1323]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="650">Distribution and natural history:</emphasis>
Known only from Resumidero, 
<collectingRegion id="498DF840567AFFCEFC084C46B6331427" box="[976,1083,1333,1354]" country="Mexico" name="Guerrero" pageId="16" pageNumber="650">Guerrero</collectingRegion>
; lives within the cave (
<figureCitation id="13722A27567AFFCEFA9B4C46B79D1426" box="[1347,1429,1333,1355]" captionStart="Figure 49" captionStartId="52.[164,243,1007,1026]" captionTargetBox="[172,1436,200,970]" captionTargetId="figure-347@52.[164,1444,195,977]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="Figure 49. Known distribution of Hemirrhagus mitchelli (Gertsch, 1982), Hemirrhagus puebla (Gertsch, 1982), Hemirrhagus ocellatus Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, Hemirrhagus gertschi Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, Hemirrhagus valdezi sp. nov., Hemirrhagus pernix (Ausserer, 1875), Hemirrhagus franckei sp. nov., Hemirrhagus reddelli (Gertsch, 1973), Hemirrhagus benzaa sp. nov., and Hemirrhagus guichi sp. nov." pageId="16" pageNumber="650">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
